BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO A bread seller, Sikiru Ayinde, who was kidnapped on Monday by yet-to-be identified kidnappers in Osun State has been released. Ayinde, popularly known as Gettin, was abducted by gunmen while traveling to Ifewara in his car to supply bread to his customers. It was revealed that the victim was abducted around 4am at the Express road enroute Iwaraja in the state. The abductors were said to have sent message to Ayinde’s community, insisting on the collection N5 milliom as ransom before the victim would be freed. The victim’s community was said to have beaten the ransom down to N150,000,00. A source noted that the community had gathered the fund to get the victim released. Confirming the victim’s release on Wednesday, the Public Relations Officer of the state police command, Yemisi Opalola, said Ayinde was released on Tuesday at about 11:30pm adding that he has been admitted in a hospital for treatment. “One Sikiru Ayinde who was kidnapped on 18/07/22 while going to distribute bread to his customers in Ifewara area has been released on 19/07/22 at about 2130hrs. He has gone for treatment at undisclosed hospital,” the PPRO said. Meanwhile, Opalola could not confirm whether at ransom was paid or not.